SIMPLE: pusher
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pusher
<hw>Push"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, pushes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who sells illegal drugs, esp. one who tries to
convince others to use such drugs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Railroad)</fld> <def>a second engine attached to
the rear of a train to provide extra power for climbing steep
grades.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pushing</ent>⟦br⟧
